Author: questions_anonymous
Text: This happens to me once in a while too, and it usually goes away on it's own; I think it's just increased blood pressure. If you're used to treadmill running, it totally makes sense this happened because that's a [way less strenuous workout] (https://www.realclearscience.com/quick_and_clear_science/2017/05/30/you_may_need_to_run_15_faster_on_a_treadmill_to_equal_running_outside.html).
